<topic id="applet_webapp_comparison">
  <title>Feature Matrix</title>
  <body>
    <p><ph keyref="webappProduct"/> was designed to provide the functionality of the
        <uicontrol>Author</uicontrol> mode in <term>Oxygen XML Editor/Author</term> in a
      mobile-friendly platform and can be embedded either in a third-party standalone Java
      application or customized as a Java Web Applet to provide WYSIWYG-like XML editing and
      reviewing directly in your choice of web browsers on your mobile devices or desktops.</p>
    <p>
      <table frame="all" rowsep="1" colsep="1" id="table_j1b_d5h_br">
        <title>Feature Matrix Showing Differences Between Web Author and Oxygen XML
          Editor/Author</title>
        <tgroup cols="3">
          <colspec colname="c1" colnum="1" colwidth="1.0*"/>
          <colspec colname="newCol2" colnum="2" colwidth="1*" align="center"/>
          <colspec colname="c3" colnum="3" colwidth="1.0*" align="center"/>
          <thead>
            <row>
              <entry>Feature</entry>
              <entry>Oxygen XML Web Author</entry>
              <entry>Oxygen XML Editor/Author</entry>
            </row>
          </thead>
          <tbody>
            <row>
              <entry>Intended audience</entry>
              <entry>Reviewers and occasional contributors.</entry>
              <entry>Content authors, technical writers.</entry>
            </row>
            <row>
              <entry>Mobile device friendly</entry>
              <entry>Specifically designed for mobile devices.</entry>
              <entry>No</entry>
            </row>
            <row>
              <entry>Compatibility with the standard versions of Oxygen </entry>
              <entry>Covers only editing and reviewing features.</entry>
              <entry>100%</entry>
            </row>
            <row>
              <entry><uicontrol>Author</uicontrol> mode</entry>
              <entry>Yes</entry>
              <entry>Yes</entry>
            </row>
            <row>
              <entry><uicontrol>Text</uicontrol> mode</entry>
              <entry>Yes</entry>
              <entry>Yes</entry>
            </row>
            <row>
              <entry><uicontrol>Grid</uicontrol> mode</entry>
              <entry>No</entry>
              <entry>Yes</entry>
            </row>
            <row>
              <entry>Schema <uicontrol>Design</uicontrol> mode</entry>
              <entry>No</entry>
              <entry>Yes</entry>
            </row>
            <row>
              <entry>Client-side setup</entry>
              <entry>Yes, with an <i>Administration</i> page.</entry>
              <entry>Requires Java to be installed, and Java Applets to be allowed to run.</entry>
            </row>
            <row>
              <entry>Server-side setup</entry>
              <entry>Requires running an installer or a servlet (along with performing a Maven
                build).</entry>
              <entry>Requires a web server.</entry>
            </row>
            <row>
              <entry>Saxon versions included</entry>
              <entry>Saxon 9 HE</entry>
              <entry>Saxon  6 and 9 (HE, PE, EE)</entry>
            </row>
          </tbody>
        </tgroup>
      </table>
    </p>
